long_desc.thetext:
we need an clear api for RepositoryConfiguration. Sometimes we use getOptionValues() in other places we use getVersions.
For bug 372592 we need to know if we need the values for * new or changed tasks or * query selection.
I create an Interface so we can have two separate classes for config.cgi and xmlrpc.
Thougths?
Create review http://review.mylyn.org/#change,335
Created attachment 211691 mylyn/context/zip
We absolutely have to wait until after 3.7 to consider this change.

I don't fully understand the purpose of the interface. I only see one implementation?
My sense is that we need to capture the differences between Bugzilla versions on the model level instead of implementing different behavior. In terms of API we can consider exposing an interface instead of an implementation class but I'm -1 on using different implementations of the configuration for config.cgi and xmlrpc.

(In reply to comment #4) > I don't fully understand the purpose of the interface. I only see one > implementation? > > My sense is that we need to capture the differences between Bugzilla versions > on the model level instead of implementing different behavior. In terms of API > we can consider exposing an interface instead of an implementation class but > I'm -1 on using different implementations of the configuration for config.cgi > and xmlrpc.
Yes I want first to separate the interface from the rest. The next step is that want to create an new implementation that store all the information from the xmlrpc interface (sort order, description, is_active ...) After this I want to change SaxConfigurationContentHandler to use the new implementation and delete the RepositoryConfiguration class.

Save of the context for http://review.mylyn.org/#change,495
Now I start with an new try with generalize the RepositoryConfiguration.
